          "id": "EULEMUR_MAYOTTENSIS",
          "name": "Eulemur mayottensis",
          "rank": "SPECIES",
          "commonName": "Mayotte lemur",
          "lineage": "True lemurs",
          "continents": [
            "Africa"
          ],
          "subspeciesCount": 0,
          "description": "A lemur endemic to Mayotte (Mahoré), the French territory in the Comoro Islands, introduced from Madagascar long before European contact — possibly by Malagasy settlers over a thousand years ago. Genetically and morphologically distinct from all Malagasy Eulemur species, probably derived from an early introduction of E. fulvus or a related species that has since diverged in isolation. Males and females are similar in colouration, brownish-grey with whitish cheek patches. The Mayotte lemur was formally described as a distinct species in 2017 based on morphological and molecular evidence. The Comoros population has no wild conspecifics, making conservation of the Mayotte population uniquely important.",
          "sourcedFrom": "generated"
        }
      ]
